265
00:30:02,859 --> 00:30:04,259
SPEAKER_23: As for me...

266
00:30:06,200 --> 00:30:10,599
SPEAKER_23: if I weren't looking for my brother,
I wouldn't be wearing this uniform.

267
00:30:36,490 --> 00:30:39,859
SPEAKER_23: Chunsheng, you really are mad.

283
00:32:13,490 --> 00:32:14,980
SPEAKER_23: No one's left.

284
00:32:16,089 --> 00:32:19,119
SPEAKER_23: Must be tens of thousands
of us trapped here.

307
00:34:12,679 --> 00:34:13,769
SPEAKER_23: Home?

383
00:47:07,250 --> 00:47:10,119
SPEAKER_23: He has served in the Liberation Army?

386
00:47:15,519 --> 00:47:17,789
SPEAKER_23: That's taking part.

391
00:47:32,809 --> 00:47:35,110
SPEAKER_23: to attend Long'er's public trial.

392
00:47:35,210 --> 00:47:38,579
SPEAKER_23: Come along and get an education.

393
00:47:40,449 --> 00:47:42,210
SPEAKER_23: What did Long'er do?

394
00:47:43,179 --> 00:47:47,449
SPEAKER_23: Because of the family home,
he's been sentenced a landlord.

450
00:52:49,920 --> 00:52:51,409
SPEAKER_23: It's all here?

451
00:52:52,389 --> 00:52:53,760
SPEAKER_23: Keep these.

452
00:52:54,130 --> 00:52:56,619
SPEAKER_23: To deliver water to the steelworks.

453
00:52:56,699 --> 00:52:58,429
SPEAKER_23: Everyone will be thirsty.

454
00:52:58,500 --> 00:53:00,130
SPEAKER_23: We'll take these.

468
00:53:49,980 --> 00:53:52,079
SPEAKER_23: It's enough for two bullets.

469
00:53:52,590 --> 00:53:55,849
SPEAKER_23: We are just two bullets short
of liberating Taiwan.

470
00:53:56,059 --> 00:53:58,030
SPEAKER_23: So let's get that metal.

501
00:58:25,789 --> 00:58:27,420
SPEAKER_23: This is too much.

718
01:22:38,149 --> 01:22:40,710
SPEAKER_23: - You're eating?
- Come on in, Mr. Niu.

719
01:22:40,779 --> 01:22:43,880
SPEAKER_23: - Don't let me interrupt.
- We're finished.

730
01:23:26,399 --> 01:23:28,119
SPEAKER_23: Latest editorial:

731
01:23:28,329 --> 01:23:30,760
SPEAKER_23: "The older, the more reactionary."

732
01:23:39,779 --> 01:23:41,739
SPEAKER_23: Do as Chairman Mao says.

736
01:24:20,250 --> 01:24:21,880
SPEAKER_23: Fetch a brazier.

738
01:24:51,380 --> 01:24:52,609
SPEAKER_23: Fugui...

765
01:26:39,789 --> 01:26:41,420
SPEAKER_23: Comrade Wan Erxi.

766
01:26:42,020 --> 01:26:43,989
SPEAKER_23: Fengxia's mom and dad.

950
01:44:06,270 --> 01:44:07,430
SPEAKER_23: Fugui!

951
01:44:11,369 --> 01:44:12,770
SPEAKER_23: Who's there?

958
01:44:33,760 --> 01:44:35,819
SPEAKER_23: It'll just take a minute.

1002
01:48:19,689 --> 01:48:21,649
SPEAKER_23: What are these eggs for?

1021
01:49:22,420 --> 01:49:24,479
SPEAKER_23: I have faith in the Party.

1024
01:49:36,399 --> 01:49:38,130
SPEAKER_23: Let's not talk about it.

1025
01:49:38,199 --> 01:49:39,859
SPEAKER_23: You go to Fengxia.

1026
01:49:40,270 --> 01:49:42,060
SPEAKER_23: Go now, I'll be okay.

1058
01:51:42,520 --> 01:51:44,550
SPEAKER_23: They've been locked away.

1059
01:51:44,930 --> 01:51:48,020
SPEAKER_23: The Red Guards are in control!

